column2: If you solder log pots (A) for HP_VOLUME, MIX_HP_LVL you don´t need to solder RL17, RL4, RL42, RL48. In other words, if you can´t find log pots for HP_VOLUME, MIX_HP_LVL, you can solder RL17, RL4, RL42 and RL48 for a fake log response on a linear potentiometer.

If you solder log pots (A) for VOLUME you don´t need to solder RL3 and RL45. In other words, if you can´t find log pots for VOLUME, you can solder RL3 and RL45 for a fake log response on a linear potentiometer.
